Class GameEventFireEvent

java.lang.Object
org.bukkit.event.Event
com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game.GameEvent
com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game.GameEventFireEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cancellable
public class GameEventFireEvent extends GameEvent implements Cancellable
Use this event to process code every time a certain GameEvent is fired
This is used for adding extra functionality to existing game events or completely overriding existing functionality by using setOverride(boolean)
Canceling this event prevents it from firing. I would not recommend doing this for GeneratorUpgradeEvent otherwise all other events should be fine
Author:
YeetManLord
API Example:
public void event(GameEventFireEvent event) {
    if (event.getFiredEvent instanceof GameEndEvent) {
      System.out.println("Game Ended");
    }
}
